main event: An observer spotted a round white object the size of a softball hovering and moving at high speed on September 7, 1956.
interesting points: The object rose to 12,000 feet and moved southeast very fast., The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes., The report indicates a strong probability that the object was a balloon., The observer was searching the area for aircraft., The report was part of Project Blue Book.
witness description: The observer was searching for aircraft, possibly a clerk.
